{
  "text": "The formal mapping errors were provided by AVISO Live Access Server (LAS) for Sea Level Anomalies. Based on these maps, the error in the Caspian Sea was 3.22 cm on average. Previous studies reported a precision range from 2 to 3.5 cm in water thickness estimated from GRACE data [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The errors in GRACE estimations decreased at higher latitudes [CITATION_6] , including the Caspian Sea region. By considering the dispersion of measurements, the investigation of uncertainty showed that the uncertainties were 3.16 and 2.84 cm for GRACE RL02 and RL03 time series respectively. Overall uncertainty of steric sea level derived from altimetry/GRACE is as follow: Where, E m is the measurement error, and the number of measurements. Without considering the thermocline precision, the SST based SSL has higher accuracy than the Altimetry and GRACE-based one.",
